After taking this course, students will be able to:
• State various measurement concepts in sports and physical education;
• distinguish major domains of assessments and evaluation in sports and physical education;
• conduct test, measurement, and evaluation of human performance in sports and physical education;
• analyze scores obtained from measurements of sports and physical education using appropriate statistical techniques and SPSS software;
• interpret the output from statistical analysis and to generate a conclusion.

At the completion of this course students will be able to:

• Demonstrate an understanding of the biomechanical principles as they apply to locomotion, sports techniques and injury prevention;
• Interpret the information gained from qualitative analyses and apply biomechanical principles to improve human performance.

By the end of the course, all students will be able to:

• Demonstrate and understand of basic sociological theories in sports and physical education;
• Identify and understand the professional problems associated with being a PE/Sport professional in Hong Kong as a way of preparing students for their role in the profession;
• Analyze social problems in sports and physical education;
• Apply learnt theories and knowledge into sporting environment and physical education settings

• Write a research paper that critically reflects the major issues facing sporting society in Hong Kong today;
• Think critically, discuss and construct possible solutions to problems in the field.

Upon the completion of this course, student will be able to:
• realize how they can use their professional preparation program to maximize their educational experience at SSPE and to explore the multitude of career opportunities within this dynamic field;
• know the professional literature and professional organizations and discuss their role in professional development;
• acquaint with the challenges and issues confronting professionals in the field.

