• conduct their teaching in a profession manner

By the end of the course, all students will be able to:

• demonstrate an understanding of the basis principles involved at the organizational and administrative levels of sport and physical education;
• outline the administrative role of the physical education teacher in the school setting;
• develop skill in the application of administrative principles that will be encountered when they assume future professional roles as physical education teachers;
• explain how managerial and administrative roles are important in the fields of sports and physical education;
• write a report that critically analyses the sporting society using concepts and theories of administration and management

Upon the completion of this course, students will be able to:

• Identify the need and interest of secondary school students of different age and learning ability;
• Select and adopt an appropriate teaching style in order to accomplish specific teaching assignment;
• Prepare, organize and deliver a unit of physical education lesson for local secondary students in a safe physical education environment;
• Plan, implement and evaluate an effective PE program that is relevant to the school situation.

After taking this course, students will be able to

• Identify the need and interest of primary school students of different age and learning ability;
• Select and adopt an appropriate teaching style in order to accomplish specific teaching assignment;
• Prepare, organize and deliver a unit of physical education lesson for local primary students in a safe physical education environment;
• Plan, implement and evaluate an effective PE program that is relevant to the school situation.

After taking this course, students will be able to

• demonstrate the knowledge and understand the principles and practices of acquiring knowledge and solving problems through research;
• use various research methods in examining a topic in sports science and physical education;
• employ online databases for academic research;
• analyse and evaluate the quality of studies published in peer-reviewed learned journals.

Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:
1. demonstrate an understanding of the importance of technology applications in sports and health;
2. identify important technology applications in the field and their core working principles;
3. demonstrate knowledge and competence in applying technology to enhance sport performances, physical education, or health promotion.

By the end of the course, students will be able to:

• Demonstrate a good understanding of a range of major sociological theories in the study of sport and society;
• Develop their knowledge and skills in the application of sociological perspectives in the study of the selected topics in sport sociology;
• Work effectively in a group in carrying out a research project on a selected topic in sport sociology and present their research report in the class competently;
• Think critically, discuss and construct possible solutions in tackling problems in the field of sport sociology.

Upon the completion of this course, students will be able to:

• understand the concepts of and approaches to using sport and exercise psychology;
• describe key approaches to understanding personality and motivation and identify how personality and motivation can be assessed;
• discuss the nature and major sources of stress and anxiety and how emotions affect performance;
• explain how competition and cooperation influence individuals;
• understand how group processes such as group cohesion, leadership and communication affect performance;
• describe goal setting principles and strategies;
• discuss causes and different models of overtraining and burnout;
• understand the causes of aggression and its relationship to performance, and

• develop a psychological skills training program and identify problems of such implementation.

Upon the completion of the course, students will be able to:
• Understand the important aspects of human growth and health education;
• Learn the normal process of human growth, development and maturation;
• Understand the biological and psychological variation evident during children and adolescent;
• Understand the effect of health education upon human growth and health;
• Understand the effect of physical activities and exercises on popular health issues;
• Analysis current issues and research of human growth and health education.

Upon the completion of the course, students will be able to:
• Learn from other professionals in the field;
• Develop future career options / opportunities;
• Develop positive attitude and responsibility;
• Develop problem solving skills;
• Develop beneficial links with the Sports Industry;
• Demonstrate ability in the planning, implementing, and evaluation of a project independently.

