After taking this course, students will be able to:

• identify major components of health-related fitness;
• stratify exercise participants into risk categories;
• perform pre-exercise screening and preparation procedures;
• perform health-related fitness tests in a safe and skillful manner;
• compute exercise intensity and energy expenditure of various forms of exercise;
• prescribe appropriate exercise prescription for healthy individuals for improving their health-related fitness.

courses.course_syllabus:
• Association between physical activity, fitness, and health;
• Pre-exercise screening and risk stratification;
• Procedures of conducting health-related fitness tests;
• Exercise testing for assessing cardiovascular fitness;
• Exercise prescription for improving cardiovascular fitness;
• Calculation of metabolic demands. in terms of HR, VO2, and energy expenditures;
• Use and interpretation of basic electrocardiogram (EKG);
• Tests for assessing body composition;
• Exercise prescription for improving body composition;
• Exercise testing for assessing muscular fitness;
• Exercise prescription for improving muscular fitness;
• Exercise testing for assessing flexibility;
• Exercise prescription for improving flexibility;
• Tests for assessing neuromuscular relaxation;
• Exercise prescription for improving neuromuscular relaxation;
• Other concerns for conducting exercise testing and exercise prescription.

